etymologies: Middle English (in an earlier sense). From Anglo-Norman zedwal, zedewal, zedewale, zedeuale, cetewale, cetual, citewal, Old French zedual, Old French, Middle French citoal, citoual, Middle French cetoal, sotoval (Palsgrave) zedoary, probably directly from Arabic zadwār

definitions: Any of several valerians, especially garden valerian, Valeriana officinalis, and red valerian, Centranthus ruber. Now chiefly historical.
